Name: Rapattack "Hard In Da Feint"
Description: Coach Doc is throwing down with this peak-hour party time match that's gonna make you feel like this boxing ring is a mosh pit.

Name: Freedom Rock "Reelin' in the Groove"

Name: Pros Only "Welcome to the Madhouse"
Description: Dive into the belly of the beast with this maelstrom of Metal that will make you feel tectonic shifts below and thunder and lightning above. Coach Mark came here to shred.

Name: Pop Till You Punk "All Hits No Misses"
Description: Fire a fistful of fiesty in the ring with Coach Leanne and these early noughties hotties.

Name: Girl Power "Global Galz"
Description: Bop around the world alongside Coach Dwana to these international female Hip Hop and Pop powerhouses. Please note, some spicy lyrics in this workout are not for the faint of heart!

Name: Sweat Symphony "Movement Masterpiece"
Description: You and Coach Dwana are taking the symphony on the road, touring through Japan and China for this special Classical course that will warm your soul and lift you into the clouds.

Name: Quick Hits Strut
Description: Coach Mark comes correct with this short-form workout of Rock bangers from the first half of the 2000s.

Name: Quick Hits Pop Till You Punk

Name: Quick Hits Superfreak

Name: Meditation "I Am Here"
Description: Take a moment to tap into your power and fully embrace the now with Guest Meditation Coach, Andrea Ming. Experience a deeper state of relaxation while improving your concentration and mindful awareness for a renewed sense of calm. This is your time to simply Be, Athlete.

Name: Reggae Getaway "Putting On A Vibe"
Description: Lay back and lean into your weekend vibe as Coach Doc leads you through this dialed in Reggae Getaway.

Name: Moment @  Clear Lake, Oregon

Name: The Drop "Get Ur Brain In The Game"
Description: Push it to the limit with Coach Leanne in this supercharged boxing workout that is sure to rev your engines.

Name: Retrofit "Tempting (retro)Fate"
Description: It's 80s night at Coach Mark's, and he's pulling out all the stops! Swing along with him on this journey through Gothy Post-Punk that's heavy on the eyeliner and teased hair, jumpy and funky Electro Pop, and cerebral Alternative guitar Funk.

Name: Prom Night "Flower Power"
Description: Travel back in time with Coach Chesney to prom night from the late 60s. Do this workout before heading out to pick up your sweetheart, just don't forget the corsage or boutonniere!

Name: Pop Till You Drop "Good4U4Sure"
Description: Box to the top of the charts alongside Coach Dwana and these current Pop hits by artists from the AAPI community as we continue to celebrate Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month.

Name: Rap-ture "Pull Up!"
Description: Somebody come get Coach Doc—he's feeling that beat with this short 'n' sweet contemporary Hip-hop Boxing bout.

Name: Just Dance "Carefree"
Description: Bring the Funk to these Dance, Pop, and Hip Hop tracks with Coach Raneir!

Name: Molten Rock "Ready for Everything"
Description: It's back to the Garage Rock revival of the mid-2000s with this fully-loaded match-up in the ring with Coach Mark.

Name: Nouveau Disco "Do What You Do"
Description: It's time to get down to the Disco sound, athlete! Dance to LoFi Funky House mixed with some Disco-inspired Pop gems - guaranteed to make you sweat!

Name: Pump, You Up 90s "Club NYC"
Description: Coach Ranier is taking you "deep inside" an NYC nightclub for a turned-up and  90s House and big-room Electronic set. Are you down?

Name: Monster "We Will Be Victorious"
Description: Muster up the strength and courage alongside Coach Mark for our debut Boxing Monster in this all-out Modern Rock mash.

Name: Quick Hits Y2K Babyyy
Description: Turn up the dial for these 2000-era rock favorites while Coach Mark leads you through a quick Boxing workout.

Name: Quick Hits Rap-ture
Description: You know that Coach Doc isn't going home, which means you're going hard in this Quick Hit Rap-ture workout.

Name: Quick Hits Retrofit
Description: Coach Mark keeps you hanging on for a Quick Hit 80s party in this boxing Retrofit.

Name: Meditation "Go Within"
Description: We are asked to be strong in every moment of our day. We look for ways to show that strength to others through our actions and ability to persevere.  Yet, at times, we are left feeling weak, disguising our pain from the world. It is time to go within. Your true strength lies within you.

Name: Strut "Kick It"
Description: Cue the horn section, athlete! Swagger through feel-good Hip Hop, R&B and blues-influenced Rock with Coach Doc.

Name: Hoedown Throwdown "Lasso Up!"
Description: It's getting rough and rowdy in this roadhouse filled with some of the best Country of the early 2000s. Coach Dwana's keeping it bright and fresh—and twangy and swinging.

Name: Moment @ Rongbuk Glacier, Tibet
Description: Sit silently in the shadow of Everest at Rongbuk Glacier in southern Tibet. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Name: A Call To Arms “En Fuego!”
Description: Get fired up with Coach Raneir to an eclectic playlist of Latin-laced EDM, Pop and Reggaeton music. Shake your hips while working your upper body to maps created specifically with fast and complicado patterns to light up your arms and shoulders.

Name: Abs-o’licious "Ab Agility"
Description: Don't put the red light on moving your body, athlete! Blast back to the 80s with Coach Raneir and tune into your core with maps designed specifically to target your abdominals and obliques.

Name: Fuego "Fuego Fiesta"
Description: It's down to Mexico for Cinco de Mayo we go with Coach Raneir. Ride along as we pop-pop-pop our way into the country's eclectic world of Pop and Rock that stretches from the intimate and folksy to the epic and oversized.

Name: Super Monster "(Hair) Metal Marathon"
Description: Travel through the eras of Glam, Metal, and Hard Rock with Coach Mark in this dramatic and muscular workout that's equal parts classic torch songs and music-discovery moments.

Name: Superfreak "Quite the Sensation"
Description: Get into the disco-funk groove with Coach Doc in this classic late 70s-era Superfreak boxing workout.

Name: Star Wars "May The 4th Be With You"
Description: In a galaxy far, far away, find the Force within to help Coach Doc triumph over the Dark Side in this heart-pumping, one-day-only Star Wars Day workout.

Name: The Drop "Don’t Close Your Eyes"
Description: Hands in the air with Coach Dwana! Nonstop euphoric big-room, peak-house here, all of it steeped in heart-swelling melody and emotional catharsis.

Name: Guilty Pleasures "If It Feels Good, Do It"
Description: Coach Doc wants to you to "bang on the drum all day" with this fun, carefree bout of late-70s and early-80s Pop that's a little bit Rock, a little New Wave, and just the right amount of goofy.

Name: Rapattack "Bubble Trouble"
Description: You won't hold back the sweat as you rock with Coach Doc in this extra spicy Rapattack workout. Join us as we kick off our celebration Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month.

Name: Just Dance "The More You Dance"
Description: Get down with Coach Dwana to this set of bouncy EDM that is sure to put some pep in your step.

Name: Quick Hits Girl Power
Description: Live it up with these two capital-L Ladies of contemporary Pop for this fun and feisty Quick Hit.

Name: Quick Hits Rock Boom Baby
Description: We're going back to the beginning of rock and roll with this Quick Hit from the progenitors of the genre.

Name: Quick Hits Hip Hop You Don't Stop
Description: Pop into this quick but punchy two-song time capsule of early-2000s Hip Hop that's all Southern sass.

Name: Rapattack "It’s in Your DNA"
Description: It's a lit Hip-hop club night with Coach Doc in this tight, spare run through some of the best Trap out there.

Name: Meditation "Take Your Time"
Description: Every day is a rush to get the next thing done, to accomplish your goal, to check off the next task. Take your time. Life is here and now. Let’s take a few minutes to slow down, breathe, take it all in, and enjoy the fact that you are here. There is no rush.

Name: Sweaty Flannel "Girls of Grunge"
Description: Meet Coach Mark's wall of distortion, feedback, and gritty guitar licks with this stomper through female-fronted 90s Grunge greats.

Name: Rock The Ages "Remixed To Be Wild"
Description: Coach Mark leads you through this remixed rock playlist that puts a new spin on some familiar tunes while you put some new dents in familiar targets.

Name: Break Stuff "For Ü"
Description: Coach Leanne is bringing some sweet, gentle melodies to an otherwise turned-up and electric rumble through high-tempo, fast-paced EDM and Dubstep.

Name: Moment @ Aoraki, New Zealand
Description: Behold the snow covered summits of Aoraki, the tallest peak in the Southern Alps and all of New Zealand. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Name: Power "Go Big"
Description: Rise up and go big with Coach Leanne in this boxing workout featuring hard-hitting rock and powerful pop from the past decade.

Name: Mood Booster "More Cowbell!"
Description: We've got a fever and the only prescription is... more Supernatural! Don't be selfish; give Coach Mark all the cowbell you've got!

Name: Retrofit "Can’t Ever Get Enough"
Description: Coach Mark is popping you into a time machine and taking you back to a New Wave Rock show in NYC circa 1985, and the cost of admission is your dancing feet.

Name: Joy "All Your Troubles are Gone!"
Description: Swing your arms and move your feet with Coach Doc while feeling the joy emanating from this positive electro pop playlist.

Name: Broken Dreams Team "Rock It All Away"
Description: Coach Leanne will help mend any broken dreams with a modern rock playlist full of intensity, just don't expect a shoulder to cry on because this workout is flowing fast.

Name: Y2K Babyyy "Never Lonely"
Description: Is it 2002 or 2022? Coach Mark thinks it can be both with this one, a sultry swing through early-2000s Pop through a Soul and R&B lens.

Name: Pop Till You Drop "Poppin' The Bass"
Description: Get that booty bouncing to the bass with Coach Leanne's boogie through contemporary Pop bops, all with a garnish of Electronic flair and a side of Dance energy for extra brightness.

Name: Dance Around The World "Parlez-vous Français?"
Description: Coach Dwana is exposing her francophile tendencies with this quick trip to France and Belgium's present-day Pop scene. Light and effervescent like an Orangina, sweet and refreshing like an ice cream Cornetto.

Name: Quick Hits Rapattack
Description: Go shawty! Coach Doc has what you need with this early-mid 00s Pop Hip Hop Boxing twofer.

Name: Quick Hits Superfreak
Description: Bring the funk into the ring with Coach Dwana to late-70s, early-80s R&B and Disco in this two song set.

Name: Quick Hits Hair Brained
Description: Punch and parry through this powerful 80s two song set with Coach Dwana.

Name: Meditation "Second Chance"
Description: It is never too late, for anything. Every day, every moment is a new beginning where you have an opportunity to decide what happens next in your life. There is no defeat or failure but rather a lesson to be learned and an opportunity to grow.

Name: Supernatural "2 Year Anniversary"
Description: Time flies when you're having fun! Today is Supernatural's second anniversary and we're so happy to have you here working out with us. This workout is guaranteed to feature your favorite coach and guaranteed to put a smile on your face.

Name: Shower Songs "Sweat, Sing and Swing"
Description: Roll down the windows and belt out these Classic Rock favorites as if you were on a road trip with Coach Raneir along for the ride in the passenger seat.

Name: Girl Power "Biting Brawl"
Description: At the intersection of heavy-duty 90s Grunge and high-glossy Pop is this ladies-in-front bout with Coach Dwana. Get ready to get licked by some hooks.

Name: Moment @ Jokulsarlon, Iceland
Description: Take in the vast skies at Jokulsarlon, a glacial lagoon in southeastern Iceland. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Name: That Feeling "Be Still My Heart"
Description: Dust off those gliding synchronized dance moves alongside Coach Dwana to these nostalgic R&B and Pop love songs from yesteryear.

Description: Coach Mark wants to show you a thing or two about the dressed-up and sassy Hard Rock that came before Glam with this confident and fun tussle.

Name: Retrofit "Power Up"
Description: Elevate your state with Coach Leanne to emotion-packed and cathartic Synth Pop and Rock from the 1980s.

Name: Mood Booster "Shimmery Sparring"
Description: Let Coach Leanne lift your spirits! Spark up your sparring to Pop Rock songs with shimmery guitar and synth lines.

Name: Freedom Rock "Joy to You and Me"
Description: Rewind the clock with Coach Doc for a nitty-gritty Classic Rock throwback that's dripping in auto grease and caked in desert sand. A smooth-talking yet brawny strum through some 70s Radio Rock faves.

Name: Cover Lover "The 80s Go 90s"
Description: Rethink the conventional with Coach Mark as 90s Pop Rock and Punk acts cover these 80s favorites.

Name: Quick Hits Y2K Babyyy

Name: Hip Hop You Don't Stop "The Golden Age"
Description: We're going old school with Coach Ranier for this bounce through 80s and 90s Manhattan, Harlem, and Queens boom-bap Rap.

Description: Get amped with Coach Leanne and these genre-bending Hip Hop collaborations. Fire up the ring, athlete!

Name: Pop Till You Drop "These Boots Were Made for Boxing"

Name: Quick Hits Superfreak

Name: Quick Hits Pop Till You Drop
Description: Hit the ring for a quick, two song workout with Coach Leanne to these undeniable Pop bang-bangers from the 2010s.

Name: Quick Hits Rock The Ages
Description: A short-form go in the ring that's got enough Glammy, Hard Rock voltage to power an entire stadium.

Description: One, two, three Modern Rockin' foot-stompers and hand-clappers brought to you by Coach Mark!

Description: Take a tour through 2000s Dance Pop, Indie Pop, and Electro with Coach Ranier in this Mood Booster.

Name: Jazz It Up "Remixed Royalty"
Description: Jazz up your workout with Coach Leanne and a playful grip of Hard Bop classics reimagined with a contemporary Electronic spark. Let's paint the town, athlete!

Name: Pros Only "Power Up"
Description: Coach Leanne is here to push you into the deep end with this turbo-charged, laser-lit spaz through some wicked Dubstep and Breaks. Can you handle it?

Name: Moment @ Abajo Peak, Utah

Name: Pop Till You Punk "Edgycation"
Description: Proudly wear your heart on your sleeve with Coach Dwana for this emotional and emotive mixtape of early-00s Pop-Punk. Swing, swing—you're in safe hands.

Name: Rock Boom Baby "One For The Money"
Description: Coach Doc's bringing you back to the early days of Bluesy Rock 'N Roll with a trio of tunes by some of the original movers and shakers.

Description: Take on Coach Doc in an 80s Synth and Dance-Pop spar that's all twinkling lights and crispy clean drums.

Description: Join Coach Ranier on the festival grounds for this just-before-dusk set of Indie Dane-Pop swingy sing-along bops. An all-out sugar rush without the actual sugar. Let's go, athlete!

Description: Get ready to go, go, go with Coach Leanne and this early-80s bundle of celebratory Classic Rock belters!

Description: Time to dance and tap it out, athlete! Channel the fancy footwork from these iconic Musical classics into your gloves with Coach Dwana.

Description: Hop in with Coach Raneir for an in-and-out Quick Hit that's a little bit Country, a little bit Rock 'n Roll.

Name: Quick Hits Just Dance
Description: Hit the dance floor with Coach Leanne for a short-form workout that's a million miles tall. Supersized-EDM beats and epic drops catapult you into the stratosphere.

Name: Quick Hits Hip Hop You Don't Stop
Description: Get down with Coach Doc to some splash drums and big bass licks in this Quick Hit.

Name: Y2K Babyyy "Makin’ Our Way To Y2K"
Description: Unleash an emotional release to these empowering and cathartic tracks from the 2000s alongside Coach Leanne.

Name: Meditation "Checking In"
Description: It is time to check in with your body and your heart. This meditation will take you through a full body scan to release tension and identify emotions trapped in your body that cause tension. This meditation has extended time to give you room to check in with self.

Name: Just Dance "Party With Me"
Description: Let loose and set your body free with Coach Doc to these fresh takes on classic R&B and Hip Hop tracks.

Name: Superfreak "Swagger"
Description: Swing, strut, and get down tonight with Coach Mark. All classic sing-along soulful boogies you'll never get enough of.

Name: Moment @ Nuorgam, Finland
Description: Chill out above the Arctic Circle in Nuorgam, Finland. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Name: Coach Karaoke
Description: You’ve sung along to your favorite songs with them, but now, the stunning voices of your favorite coaches’ are the soundtrack for our newest workout series: Coach Karaoke.

Name: Pop Till You Drop "EmPOWered"
Description: Join Coach Doc for a set of uplifting and empowering Pop Rock from the 2010s!

Name: Molten Rock "Heart of a Lion"
Description: Storm your way right into this epic Modern Rock concert with Coach Mark as your guide. All no-nonsense belters with a thirst for power and a fire in the belly.

Name: Hip Hop You Don't Stop "Power In Choice"
Description: Coach Doc's gonna have y'all jumpin' back in time to a Hip Hop house party circa '95, with as much sweat dripping from the ceiling as your chin.

Name: Broken Dreams Team "Finding Emo"
Description: Cut loose and let unleash the inner-angsty teen for this Pop-Punk mosh with Coach Ranier.

Name: The Drop "Fire Burnin'"
Description: This selection of Big Room house bangers is so buttery-smooth that Coach Mark might as well be a pastry chef. Order up, athlete!

Name: Strut "Rowdy Rock"
Description: Stomp, whomp, and roll right on through this bout with Coach Mark that's all chunky, chuggin' 70s Glam.

Name: Super Monster "Perseverance"
Description: Celebrate the perseverance of the powerful women in your life with 45-minutes of non-stop diva Disco dancing. Dive in with Coach Dwana as we continue to celebrate Women's History Month.

Name: Cover Lover "Decades of Dance"
Description: Join Coach Dwana under cover of darkness for a club-leaning set of covers that bring extra zip to these classics tracks.

Name: Quick Hits Molten Rock
Description: Rock out those riffs in the ring with Coach Mark to Alternative Rock from the 00s and 10s in this two song set.

Name: Quick Hits The Drop
Description: Bring the Big Room energy to this brawl with Coach Doc in a short-form workout.

Name: Quick Hits Power
Description: Conquer powerful combos with Coach Mark to two Electronic-laced Modern Rock tracks in this Quick Hit.

Name: Meditation "Internal Compass"
Description: To allow yourself a life worthy of your best self, you must know where you are headed. Your internal compass guides all that you do, everywhere you go, and to whom your love shall be granted. Take the time in this meditation to reflect upon your North Star.

Name: Retrofit "Lost in Motivation"
Description: Float back to the 1980s with Coach Dwana and these misty yet dreamlike New Wave classics.

Name: Rock Hard "Break to Breathe"
Description: Turn up the chunky distortion with this darker-leaning, moody Nu-Metal from the early-2000s. Rock on with Coach Doc and a set that increases in energy from start to finish.

Name: Shower Songs "Highly Wily"
Description: Join Coach Leanne for a zippy journey through (mostly) 90s Alt Rock and Brit Pop. Warm up those vocal chords for this playful playlist!

Name: Just Dance "Eyes Wide Open"
Description: Get ready for the weekend with this bright and bouncy Dance Pop set. Bring the party into the ring with Coach Doc!

Name: Moment @ Lac de Peyrelade, France
Description: Hang in the grassy hills of Lac de Peyrelade in Hautes-Pyrénées, France. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Name: Joy "Do It For Yourself"
Description: Get your smile on with Coach Mark. Juicy beats and sweet lyrics guaranteed in this 2010s Pop set!

Name: Guilty Pleasures "Fire in Your Desire"
Description: Gear up for a night out with Coach Raneir! Dial into these dreamy yet moody 80s club smashes.

Name: Rapattack "Give It To Me"

Name: Sweaty Flannel "Sweaty, Not Sweety"
Description: Coach Dwana says... it's the early 90s and time to strap in for a gnarly glob of Grunge grease. Keep those abs tight—a real gut-punch is coming your way.

Name: Girl Power "Self Respect"
Description: Coach Doc's gonna get you swinging those fists along to swinging, soulful R&B ballads of empowerment and inner-strength as we celebrate Women's History Month.

Name: Pros Only "Underground Grime"
Description: Go deep into the London underground with Coach Leanne for a dank, raw mix of Trap and Grime that you'll immediately find yourself jumpin', jumpin' along to.

Name: Disney Hits "Encanto"
Description: Find your inner strength and spread your magic in Disney Hits: Encanto! Break a sweat with Coach Doc as you belt along to this epic and inspiring soundtrack that is taking the world by storm. We might not talk about Bruno, but we do work out with him.

Name: Hair Brained "Burn With Me"
Description: Hose yourself down with hairspray and squeeze into your leather leggings for this epic Glam-Metal thrasher. Join the band with Coach Leanne keeping you tied to the chugging beat.

Name: Quick Hits Pros Only "Abs-o’licious"
Description: Level up with two higher than high intensity maps specifically targeting your abdominals and obliques with Coach Raneir.

Name: Quick Hits Pop Till You Drop
Description: Top the charts with Coach Dwana and these current Top 40 favorites in a short-form workout.

Name: Quick Hits Y2K Babyyy
Description: Channel your inner-Pop diva with Coach Raneir and these 2000s hits in this two song set.

Name: Stretching "Full-Body Stretch"
Description: Being in-tune with your body can help prevent small tweaks from becoming major setbacks. Join Coach Mark, and take a few minutes to honor and care for yourself today with a full body stretch.

Name: Broken Dreams Team "Bring The Storm"
Description: Coach Leanne will stitch that heart of yours back together with these triumphant Pop-Punk anthems that overcome obstacles with a lotta guitar and a lotta boom-bap drum-machine beats.

Name: Pump, You Up 90s "Try A Little"
Description: Coach Mark will shuffle you through the folksier, twangier side of the Hard Rock and Grunge 90s. Warm and rollicking, this one's more campfire singalongs than basement moshpits.

Name: Moment @ Varlaam Monastery, Greece
Description: Climb the cliff of Meteora to set your sights on the Varlaam Monastery in Greece. To enjoy this moment without music, hit the menu button on your left controller to adjust the volume. [Experimental]

Description: Give yourself some space with this low impact workout perfect for athletes looking to focus on big hits and broad movements.

Name: Glutacious "Ooh La La"
Description: Say goodbye to your glutes, because this mix is all about those triangles! Get low, sweaty, and feel the burn with this fun mix of medium intensity favorites to get you in the mood to move. Start with some shoulder openers and squats to warm up, then dive in!

Name: Retrofit "Swept Away"
Description: You may not be ready for this one! Join Raneir in a high energy, high tempo 80s cardio blast perfect for athletes looking to push their limits!

Name: Dark Forces "Debut"
Description: Join Coach Leanne and let the rhythm take control with this dark and dangerous mix of EDM hits! This workout is perfectly balanced for athletes looking for a fun challenge.

Name: Just Dance "Bring the Action"
Description: Are you ready for a dance party? Get moving to this awesome mix of fast paced Pop tracks designed to get you feeling the burn!

Name: Skinny Jeans and Ripped Seams "Magnetic"
Description: This fun, upbeat mix of Indie favorites is sure to get you feeling ready to tackle your week! Start with some leg raises to loosen up the lower body, then dive in with tracks from Edward Sharpe & The Magnetic Zeros, Of Monsters and Men, and Saint Motel!

Name: Rapattack “Sweat Equity”
Description: Get ready to work! Maintain a faster pace to your strikes, squats, and lunges while jamming out to some modern Hip Hop favorites! Prepare yourself for an all-out Rap attack!

Name: Meditation "K.I.S.S."
Description: Take a seat, settle in, and spend 10 minutes connecting with the self in this meditation focused on the elegance of simplicity. Keep It Simple and Sacred, athlete.

Name: Mood Booster "Continuous Flow"
Description: Boost through the ages! Every song is a new decade in this Pop mix of mood boosters, starting out with "I Can't Help Myself (Sugar Pie, Honey Bunch)" from 1965! Follow it up with a 70s trip by Faces, then keep smashing targets into the 00s with Young the Giant!

Name: Sweaty Flannel "You're Alright"
Description: A fun collection of Alt Rock favorites focused on steady, intentional movement. Start out with chest and hip openers to prepare the body to move, then dive in with hits from Third Eye Blind, Violent Femmes, and Supergrass!

Name: Strut "Break Free"
Description: Take up space and show the world what you're made of with this fun mix of low intensity throwback favorites.

Name: Freedom Rock "Warrior"
Description: A feel-good workout with some of our favorite Rock classics. This is a great workout for athletes looking to swing big while still maintaining a fun cardio pace. Start off with The Velvet Underground's "Sweet Jane," then trip out with "Smoke On The Water," "Sunshine Of Your Love," and "Ramblin' Man"!

Name: Power "Debut"
Description: Maintain a faster, more vigorous pace with this one! Coach Doc starts off with easy prep work to get you feeling agile, then warms you up with Volbeat. Keep it going with a high intensity mix of hardcore tracks from Jet, Shinedown, Bassnectar, and Knife Party!

Name: Pump, You Up 90s "Turn on, Tone in"
Description: Get your week started right with the perfect pick-me-up from the best decade ever! Start with a quick squat tutorial with Leanne, then dive in with some awesome, off-beat 90s favorites from Snap!, and Reel 2 Real!

Name: Slow Burn "Joy"
Description: Tap into the body and the mind with another Slow Burn Sunday. Get moving with Coach Doc, then dive into some excellent slow-your-roll favorites. Don't forget to stick around after the cooldown for a short meditation to recenter!

Name: Y2K Babyyy "Debut"
Description: Timewarp to the T9 era with this fantastic mix of Pop classics! Join Raneir in some sumo squats to get into the legs and glutes, get warmed up with "All Falls Down" by Kanye, then start smashing those targets!

Name: Monster "Heavy"
Description: Get ready for another monster! This workout is made for athletes looking to build endurance and test their agility with some of our toughest tracks yet! Get into the body with some practice lunges and chest openers, then dive in with these Pop and Rock hits!

Name: Strut "Debut"
Description: An uplifting, confidence-boosting mix of Indie favorites designed to get you moving with swagger! Start out with trunk twists and side lunges to get into the body, warm up with "Some Nights" by Fun., then start strutting your stuff with tracks from Grouplove, LCD Soundsystem, and OK Go! [Medium Intensity]

Name: Flow: Getting Started
Description: The perfect workout to begin your Supernatural journey! This workout breaks down the basics of Flow to get you comfortable striking targets to the beat and squatting and lunging into triangles. Come back and repeat whenever you want to practice or perfect your moves.

Name: Rock Hard "Debut"
Description: Prepare thyself, mortal! This all-Metal workout pulls no punches! Start out by waking up the shoulders and the core, then practicing some side lunges to warm up the lower body. Rock on, athlete!

Name: Just Dance "Debut"
Description: Get ready for a dance party in your living room! Focus on fun, free movement and getting into the rhythm of the songs. Warm up with a few squats and chest openers, then dive in to some of our favorite Dance tracks with Katy Perry, David Guetta, and The Knocks!

Name: Slow Burn "Kiara"
Description: Breathe deep, find your center, and ease into the perfect Sunday wind-down with Coach Doc. This is a 20 minute workout made to focus on proper movement for shattering targets with power and purpose.

Name: Meditation "One"
Description: Tap in with this 10 minute meditation to build energy and relax. Excellent if you're looking to recharge following a workout, or simply to recenter! Coach Doc leads you through some breathing, while leaving you space to focus on the self and the present moment.

Name: Pool House "The 4th"
Description: It’s time to celebrate, baby! Jump into this high flying, sure-to-get-you-sweating workout with some of our favorite Tropical House tracks just perfect for a socially distanced Fourth of July dance party!

Name: Guilty Pleasures "Debut"
Description: Let's get indulgent! Check your cool at the door, 'cause this eclectic mix of guilty pleasure tunes is designed to get you rocking out like nobody's watching! This is an interval workout starting with High Intensity, easing off into Medium, then back into High

Name: Skinny Jeans and Ripped Seams "Irresistible"
Description: Pull on those skinny jeans and let's get down! This challenging but approachable playlist starts out with some fun, free-flowing movement with Raneir, then serves up some of our favorite Electro Pop tracks.

Name: Girl Power "Good Times"
Description: Join Leanne for an incredible workout with some of our favorite female artists from the 60s and 70s! Start with some breathing and side lunges to get into the body, then let the good times roll with Chic, Chaka Khan, and Diana Ross!

Name: The Drop "Liquid Bonfire"
Description: This is an all-Dubstep playlist with high-tempo, high intensity tracks perfect for athletes looking for that extra challenge. This is great for cardio exercise and working your upper body, including shoulders, chest, and upper back.

Name: Mood Booster "Debut"
Description: Get ready for an energetic boost, baby! We've got a truly amazing mix of upbeat Indie Rock favorites sure to lift your spirits and get you moving with passion.

Name: Slow Burn "Chi"
Description: Your Sunday Slow Burn is here! Limber up with Coach Doc to get the body moving, then jump into it! Start shattering targets with Dua Lipa, Lorde, and Nick Jonas, then bring it home with a cooldown followed by a short, three minute meditation!

Name: Pep It Up
Description: Pep up your day with this fun interval workout! Alternate between low and medium intensity tracks to build endurance. This is perfect for athletes looking to work their way from Low to Medium intensity workouts.

Name: Heat
Description: A high-tempo cardio blast with a fun mix of Rock tracks to get you moving with agility and strength! Heat up with Violent Femmes' "Blister In the Sun," then keep it going with more high intensity tracks from Royal Blood, Blur, and Jet!

Name: Freedom Rock "Ramblin' Man"
Description: Join Coach Doc on a fitness road trip! This medium intensity workout starts with an easy-going warmup from Fleetwood Mac, then picks up speed with The Monkees. Keep things steady with Faces, then close it out with more classics from The Allman Brothers Band!

Name: Work It
Description: A fun mix of dancey, low intensity tracks with a bit of an aggressive flair! This workout is perfect for getting into the body while still having the time and the space to WORK IT!

Name: Punk You "Debut"
Description: Go Punk yourself! This high complexity, high intensity workout puts you through the ringer with classic Punk hits from The Stooges, Richard Hell, and DEVO!

Name: Pump, You Up 90s "Debut"
Description: Leanne is here to pump up the jam with this medium intensity 90s throwback! Get warmed up with Stone Temple Pilots, then pull on some in-lines and your favorite denim jacket for "Semi-Charmed Life" by Third Eye Blind!

Name: Slow Burn "Breathe"
Description: Coach Doc is here for another Sunday Slow Burn! This low intensity, shorter-duration workout is followed by a meditation. Focus on giving yourself the time to align breathing and body movement so each strike, lunge, and squat are executed with purpose!

Name: Monster "Help Me"
Description: Leanne is here with another marathon workout! Get ready for a high tempo challenge built for advanced athletes who don't know when to quit! Start out with chest openers and quad/hip stretches, then strap in for 30+ minutes of high intensity movement! [High Intensity]

Name: Pride
Description: Join Raneir for a celebration of Pride and being true to yourself. This high paced, medium intensity workout is all about joyful and energetic movement.

Name: Superfreak "Get Ur Freak On"
Description: Raneir is back with some of your favorite Motown hits! This low intensity workout is meant to challenge you as you move to the beat. Groove your way into “Rescue Me” for a dynamic warmup, then turn up the heat with Marvin Gaye, Four Tops, and The Jackson 5!

Name: Incline
Description: Get ready for a journey! Imagine this interval workout as rugged terrain, taking you up in intensity, back down, and then up yet again! Start out with a hard-hitting warmup with Kaleo, then set out on the trail with Nightish, Jay Golden, and Lizzo!

Name: The Drop "Out of My Mind"
Description: Get ready for our most extreme drop yet! This is a high intensity Dubstep workout that starts fast and stays fast! Practice high agility patterns that work your arms, chest, and shoulders while putting you through some excellent cardio exercises!

Name: Fitness Journey "Debut"
Description: Join Leanne as she takes you through how to set yourself up for a motivating and inspiring fitness journey. This workout launched our Fitness Journey contest. See the winners and read the stories of their journeys on our Instagram @getsupernatural.

Name: Slow Burn "Smile"
Description: Settle in for another Slow Burn with Coach D! This workout is great for active recovery days, or for focusing on form and follow-through. Don't forget to stay until the end for a quick meditation to tap in and re-center!

Name: Flow "Debut"
Description: Get moving with this approachable, flowing playlist with a fun mix of Pop hits! Leanne's prepared a slightly longer cooldown for you, so stick around to the very end for some hamstring stretches and breathing exercises!

Name: Skinny Jeans and Ripped Seams "Debut"
Description: Get ready for an Indie Rock workout! Start out by working on your posture with back and chest openers, then dive in for a medium intensity playlist with Young the Giant, alt-J, and Sir Sly!

Name: Move It
Description: Let's get moving! Raneir is here with a fun, chilled-out mix of Pop tracks to get you out of your head and into that body!

Name: Monster "Feels So Good"
Description: Get ready to sweat! This is a 30-minute, high intensity workout designed to put your abilities to the test. Get warmed up and dive right in! This workout is built for agility training, so focus on your breathing, and never stop moving!

Name: Retrofit "Totally Tubular"
Description: Let's do the timewarp again! Raneir is here with an EXCELLENT 80s playlist with some totally tubular hits! Start off with some high velocity practice swings to get warmed up, then dive into our favorite throwback playlist to date!

Name: Slow Burn "The Gift"
Description: Tap in and get moving with another Slow Burn with Coach Doc. Focus on your breathing and the sensations in your body as you shatter those targets with intention and follow-through.

Name: The Drop "Bullet Proof"
Description: Prepare yourself for another EDM onslaught! This high intensity workout is both a mental AND physical challenge, perfect for athletes looking to test their abilities and go all out!

Name: The Turn Up
Description: This is Raneir's personally-curated dance party playlist, built from the ground up to brighten your day and get you turned UP! This medium intensity workout ramps up, hits a peak, then eases you back down to Earth to close out the party!

Name: Pop Till You Punk "Debut"
Description: Let's get emo! Leanne is here with an incredible Pop Punk playlist with all of our favorite eyeliner-wearing artists! This is a high intensity playlist, so prepare for lots of cardio work and agility training!

Name: Monster "Don't Stop Me"
Description: Leanne is here with another 30-minute MONSTER of a workout! Get ready for a test of endurance with this awesome mix of medium intensity throwback tracks! Get started with some lower body work, then ease into your mid-week workout with these classic hits!

Name: Go Big
Description: Coach Raneir shows how to take up space, follow-through with your swings, and go Big. This is a low intensity workout, so take advantage of the time between targets to focus on active core engagement and proper squat form.

Name: Sweaty Flannel "Debut"
Description: Dig out that flannel, 'cause we're heading back to the 90s! This medium intensity workout is the perfect way to start your week on a high note. Get warmed up with STP, turn it up to Sugar Ray then start sweating with Third Eye Blind, Barenaked Ladies, and Blur!

Name: Slow Burn "Love Yourself"
Description: It's time for your Sunday Slow Burn! Coach Doc is here to get that body moving with power and ease, perfect for low intensity work or a recovery day. Stick around after the cooldown for another quick meditation!

Name: Pool House "Debut"
Description: Raneir is here to throw you your own personal pool party! Enjoy medium intensity House tracks and remixes built to lift you up and get you sweating. Start out with A R I Z O N A and The Knocks, then end big with "I Miss You" by Clean Bandit.

Name: Rapattack "Heart Pumpin"
Description: Another all-out rap attack, this time with Coach Doc leading the charge. This high intensity full body workout will test your endurance and push you to to the limit. Start out with The Next Episode then continue cranking up the intensity all the way to the end!

Name: Dive In
Description: Leanne is here with an excellent, medium intensity workout all about diving deep and finding your inner strength. Start out by loosening up the shoulders, then jump in with OK Go, The Knocks and Twenty One Pilots!

Name: Staying Power
Description: An approachable, yet challenging workout with a fun mix of Alt Rock and Indie favorites. Dig deep, find your strength, and show some staying power! [Low Intensity]

Name: Sustain
Description: Put your endurance to the test and get ready for a 30-minute total body journey!

Name: Pop Till You Drop "Make Your Mark"
Description: Get your week started with a pitch perfect collection of our newest Pop tracks! Nick Jonas, and Lorde join for a Memorial Day celebration in your living room. Get ready to cut loose, have fun, and smash those targets with strength and accuracy!

Name: Slow Burn "Gratitude"
Description: A low intensity workout that's all about improving your physical and mental well-being. Coach Doc is here to help you focus on powerful strikes, full-body movement and good vibes. Stick around after the cooldown for a quick meditation to get re-centered!

Name: Girl Power "Like A Girl"
Description: Get ready for some of our favorite female artists with another Girl Power! This medium intensity workout was made to get things burning with a little more focus on cardio movement and faster patterns.

Name: Rapattack "We Went to War"
Description: Ready for round two? This is your chance to play our favorite high intensity rap tracks at medium intensity! More time to hit powerfully, sink into the choreography, and move with intelligence.

Name: Retrofit "Chair & Leg Warmers"
Description: Retrofit is back again with an all-80s blast from the past! Let yourself get BIG with this low intensity workout made for athletes looking to take up space and lean into their strikes with power!

Name: Molten Rock "Debut"
Description: Prepare yourself for a high energy, high intensity playlist with some of our favorite modern and indie rock classics! This workout is for athletes looking for nonstop, explosive movements and cardio-heavy work. Get big, get crazy, and rock out!

Name: The Drop "Debut"
Description: Looking for an EDM shock to the senses? These ballistic house remixes will challenge your brain just as much as your body. Make sure to save your energy for an explosive glute-buster finale set to "Gecko (Overdrive)" from Oliver Heldens and Becky Hill.

Name: Follow Through
Description: Get your week started right with a quick medium intensity workout made to get you following through on every swing! Remember to wind up and strike from the core with POWER!

Name: Slow Burn "Debut"
Description: Coach Doc is here for a perfect wind-down workout. This is perfect for athletes looking for low-intensity, approachable movements with lots of room to swing and get into the body. Start slow, work smart and end with simple stretching and breathing.

Name: Peak Power
Description: Prepare for a journey! This all-Rock workout is all about meeting a challenge and not giving up. Find the power to climb the mountain ahead of you and conquer anything between you and your goal!

Name: Freedom Rock "Debut"
Description: Leanne is here with the perfect Classic Rock playlist tuned for athletes who crave the open road, but aren't wanting to put the pedal to the metal. Big, sweeping movements, fewer squats and lunges, and excellent tunes to keep you company along the way!

Name: Full Body Werk
Description: Form and function are integral to healthy body movement. Raneir is here with a medium intensity workout perfectly suited for athletes looking to pay close attention to their bodies while moving powerfully from the core!

Name: Superfreak "Debut"
Description: Get ready for a funky throwback, superfreak! Raneir leads a lower intensity workout of funk classics perfect for athletes looking for a little more room to focus. Start out easy with Hot Chocolate, turn it up with Chic, then get POWERFUL with Chaka Khan!

Name: Monster "Debut"
Description: Leanne is here with one monster of a workout. This absolute beast starts out strong and doesn't let up, with a fresh mix of high-BPM songs designed to start at a higher pace and hold that intensity throughout. Get ready for a real test of endurance!

Name: Pop Till You Drop "Debut"
Description: A fun, modern playlist with a healthy blend of upbeat, powerful vocals and awesome rhythms. Start out with some easy shoulder rolls and squats to get into the body, then prepare for a challenging all-Pop playlist perfect for athletes used to medium intensity who are looking to push their limits! [Medium Intensity]

Name: Wild
Description: This workout is all about getting big and going all out. Spread those wings in some massive, open spaces and get WILD! Raneir is here to get you moving bigger, swinging more powerfully, and squatting deeper than you ever have before. [Auto Intensity]

Name: Rapattack "Debut"
Description: Coach Doc will push your boundaries with this all out rap attack designed from the ground up to get you MOVING. Start out with a chill beat, steadily ramp up the pace, and end on max intensity!

Name: Out There
Description: Raneir is here to rock that body with some awesome, high intensity tracks to get you moving, grooving, and feeling like your best self! Get out there, baby!!

Name: Retrofit "Debut"
Description: A throwback workout perfect for beginners or more advanced athletes looking for a less intense workout on a rest day. Leanne has prepared an awesome, retro playlist full of 60, 70s, and 80s classics which are sure to get you sweating!

Name: Girl Power "Debut"
Description: Ready to experience girl power? Leanne is here with an awesome playlist with some of our favorite female artists! Get moving with some quick lunges and squats and rotational work, then dive in and get sweating!

Name: Fortify
Description: Get fortified! Coach Doc takes you on a heroic journey to some wild locations with a few of our favorite Hip Hop tracks. Let's move!!

Name: Rumble
Description: Are you ready to move? Leanne has prepared an excellent playlist of hard-hitting, high-intensity tracks designed to get you SWEATING! Let's rumble!

Name: Perfect Day
Description: Your perfect day has arrived! Raneir is here to take you on a happy-go-lucky journey through a dancey, up-beat playlist that's sure to get you sweating!

Name: Balance
Description: Strike a balance between cardio movement and strength building. Leanne takes you on a quick 13-minute workout adventure designed to get you working your body and mind! [Auto Intensity]

Name: Transform
Description: True transformation takes hard work and dedication. Get big, get bold, and get determined! Leanne leads you through a top-shelf playlist all about focusing on the self, and making big changes.

Name: The Present
Description: Take a deep breath and get centered as Leanne guides you back into the present moment.

Name: Power Jams
Description: Focus on the power of your movements as Coach Doc turns your workout into a hurricane!

Name: Pros Only "Debut"
Description: Mastered the rest? This workout challenges even the best. Leanne is calling you out, do you accept? This workout is locked at Hard and does not adjust based on performance.

Name: Beginners Only
Description: Perfect for people new to Supernatural. Leanne eases you into this workout as you move to hits from top artists.

Name: Funout
Description: It’s time to get absolutely crazy and have some fun with Raneir as you work your body to high energy tracks.

Name: Tough
Description: Coach Doc helps you strengthen your core with a full-body effort. Get ready to squat, lunge, and strike your way through this tough workout.

Name: Joy "Debut"
Description: Just let go with Leanne as she helps you celebrate the joy of movement.
